50|$|Settlement {{would often}} provide for payment of <b>an</b> <b>annuity</b> <b>to</b> the widow (jointure). Provision {{could be made}} for the younger {{children}} of the landowner by giving them a capital sum on reaching a certain age or getting married (portions). These were capital sums designed to set them up for life. They were secured by charging them on the land.|$|R
