50|$|In 1984, Young {{signed a}} record 10-year, $40 million {{contract}} with the USFL's Los Angeles Express. He agreed to take his payment {{in the form of}} <b>an</b> <b>annuity</b> <b>to</b> help the fledgling team; he would receive $40 million paid out over 40 years. It was reported that he would still be paid until 2027 because he insured the contract. However, in a 1985 article the Los Angeles Times stated that he received a $1.4 million settlement on the annuity.|$|R
